<p>I have a very simple directive (named <code>cooperate-with-ng-change</code>) which requires <code>ng-model</code> and I'd like it to cooperate with <code>ng-change</code>.</p>  <p>Restated, I'd like to be able to do <code>&lt;cooperate-with-ng-change ng-model="model" ng-change="changeHandler()"&gt;&lt;/cooperate-with-ng-change&gt;</code></p>  <p>However I'm noticing when <code>changeHandler()</code> is fired, <code>model</code> is the old value and not the new one.</p>  <p>Here's the directive definition object:</p>  <pre><code>return {     restrict: "E",     require: ["ngModel"],     scope: {       "value": "=ngModel"     },     template: "&lt;label&gt;Cooperate with NgChange: &lt;input type='text' ng-model='value' ng-model-options='{debounce: 500}' /&gt;&lt;/label&gt;",     link: function(scope, element, attrs, ctrls) {       var inputNgModelCtrl = element.find("input").controller("ngModel");       var parentNgModelCtrl = ctrls[0];         Array.prototype.push.apply(inputNgModelCtrl.$viewChangeListeners, parentNgModelCtrl.$viewChangeListeners)        //if I wrap all the parentNgModelCtrl.$viewChangeListeners in a timeout and digest in changeHandler       //then message matches afterDebounce       /*Array.prototype.push.apply(inputNgModelCtrl.$viewChangeListeners,         parentNgModelCtrl.$viewChangeListeners.map(           function(listener) {             return function() {               setTimeout(listener, 1)             }           }))       */     }   } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://plnkr.co/edit/GUBgNJxV4pilJpMxloXh" rel="nofollow">Here's a plunker link if you want to play with it</a></p>  <p>My guess is <code>$viewChangeListeners</code> gets called before the model value is set, however I can't find what might correspond for after the model value is set.</p>